<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 494/97 of 18 March 1997 modifying Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2868/88 establishing detailed rules for the application of the Joint International Inspection Scheme adopted by the North-West Atlantic Fisheries Organization (NAFO) </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 494/97, millega muudetakse komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2868/88, millega kehtestatakse Loode-Atlandi kalastusorganisatsiooni (NAFO) poolt vastuv&otilde;etud rahvusvahelise &uuml;hisinspekteerimise kava &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad 18. m&auml;rts 1997 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1956/88 of 9 June 1988 (1), establishing detailed rules for the application of the Joint International Inspection Scheme adopted by the North-West Atlantic Fisheries Organization as last amended by Council Regulation (EC) No 3067/95 (2) and in particular Article 4 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 9. juuni 1988. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1956/88, (1) millega kehtestati Loode-Atlandi kalastusorganisatsiooni poolt vastu v&otilde;etud rahvusvahelise &uuml;hisinspekteerimise kava rakendamise &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad, mida on viimati muudetud n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 3067/95, (2) eriti selle artiklit 4, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2868/88 (3) fixes certain rules for the implementation of the Joint International Inspection Scheme and Council Regulation (EEC) No 1956/88; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2868/88 (3) kehtestati teatavad eeskirjad rahvusvahelise &uuml;hisinspekteerimise kava ja m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1956/88 rakendamise suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Council in the interests of improving control and the enforcement of measures within the NAFO Regulatory Area, has adopted Council Regulation (EC) No 3067/95 and modified Regulation (EEC) No 1956/88 with respect to the Joint International Inspection Scheme; </inglise>
<eesti> kontrolli- ja j&otilde;ustamismeetmete parandamiseks NAFO tsoonis on n&otilde;ukogu vastu v&otilde;tnud m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 3067/95 ja muutnud m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1956/88 rahvusvahelise &uuml;hisinspekteerimise kava osas; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is appropriate to establish detailed rules for the application of new provisions of the said scheme particularly those concerning the inspection of community fishing vessels operating in the NAFO zone and presumed to have committed a major apparent infringement; </inglise>
<eesti> on asjakohane kehtestada k&otilde;nealuse kava uute s&auml;tete &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad, eelk&otilde;ige nende s&auml;tete osas, mis k&auml;sitlevad NAFO tsoonis tegutsevate &uuml;henduse kalalaevade inspekteerimist, mille puhul oletatakse ilmset t&otilde;sist rikkumist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is appropriate that details of the competent authorities of the Member States concerned should be listed in the Annex to this regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> on asjakohane, et andmed asjaomaste liikmesriikide p&auml;devate asutuste kohta esitatakse k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is therefore appropriate to modify Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2868/88; </inglise>
<eesti> seep&auml;rast tuleb komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2868/88 muuta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures adopted by the regulation are in conformity with the opinion of the Management Committee for Fisheries and Aquaculture, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses vastu v&otilde;etud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las kalanduse ja akvakultuuri korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EEC) No 2868/88 is hereby amended as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2868/88 j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The following Articles 4 (a) and 4 (b) are inserted: </inglise>
<eesti> Lisatakse j&auml;rgmised artiklid 4a ja 4b: </eesti>
<inglise> 'Article 4 (a) </inglise>
<eesti> "Artikkel 4a </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the appropriate authorities of the flag Member State are notified, pursuant to paragraph 10 (iii) of the Annex to Regulation (EEC) No 1956/88, by a NAFO inspector of an apparent serious infringement, as listed in paragraph 9 of the Annex to Regulation (EEC) No 1956/88, committed by a fishing vessel flying its flag or where the Commission receives such information, these appropriate authorities and the Commission shall immediately inform each other thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui lipuliikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused saavad NAFO inspektorilt vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1956/88 lisa punkti 10 alapunktile iii teabe selle riigi lipu all s&otilde;itva laeva sooritatud ilmsest t&otilde;sisest rikkumisest, mis on nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1956/88 lisa punktis 9, v&otilde;i kui komisjon saab niisuguse teabe, teatavad need p&auml;devad asutused ja komisjon sellest viivitamata teineteisele. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> As a result of receiving the information pursuant to paragraph 1 and of being notified by another Contracting Party or by Community inspectors assigned to the scheme of an apparent serious infringement as listed in paragraph 9 of the Annex to Regulation (EEC) No 1956/88, committed by a Community vessel, the Commission in cooperation with the flag Member State, shall ensure that the vessel is inspected within 72 hours by a duly authorized inspector. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjon on vastavalt l&otilde;ikele 1 saanud teiselt lepingupoolelt v&otilde;i kavas osalevalt &uuml;henduse inspektorilt teavet, et &uuml;henduse laev on sooritanud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1956/88 lisa punktis 9 nimetatud ilmse t&otilde;sise rikkumise, peab komisjon koost&ouml;&ouml;s lipuliikmesriigiga tagama, et n&otilde;uetekohaselt volitatud inspektor kontrollib laeva 72 tunni jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission and the flag Member State shall cooperate in order to determine as soon as possible if the inspection referred to in paragraph 2 is to be conducted by a Community inspector assigned to the scheme or by an inspector designated by the appropriate authorities of the flag Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon ja lipuliikmesriik teevad koost&ouml;&ouml;d, et v&otilde;imalikult kiiresti kindlaks teha, kas l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud inspekteerimise peab l&auml;bi viima kavas osalev &uuml;henduse inspektor v&otilde;i liikmesriigi p&auml;devate asutuste nimetatud inspektor. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The duly authorized inspector shall board the fishing vessel concerned and shall examine the elements that make up the apparent serious infringement detected by the NAFO inspector and shall as soon as possible transmit to the appropriate authority of the flag Member State and to the Commission the results of his examination. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;uetekohaselt volitatud inspektor asub asjaomase kalalaeva pardale, uurib NAFO inspektori poolt kindlaks tehtud ilmse t&otilde;sise rikkumise tunnuseid ja edastab nii kiiresti kui v&otilde;imalik lipuliikmesriigi p&auml;devale asutusele ja komisjonile selle uurimise tulemused. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Following the notification of his results and if the apparent infringement is serious, in accordance with the definition of infringements in paragraph 9 of the Annex to Regulation (EEC) No 1956/88, the appropriate authority of the flag Member State shall, if the situation requires, within 24 hours, itself require or authorize the duly authorized inspector to require the vessel to proceed to a designated port in accordance with paragraph 10 (ii) of the Annex to Regulation (EEC) No 1956/88. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;rast uurimistulemuste teatamist ja juhul, kui ilmne rikkumine on t&otilde;sine vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1956/88 lisa punktis 9 esitatud rikkumiste m&auml;&auml;ratlustele, annab lipuliikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus ise, kui olukord seda n&otilde;uab, v&otilde;i volitab n&otilde;uetekohaselt volitatud inspektorit andma 24 tunni jooksul korraldust, et laev p&ouml;&ouml;rduks m&auml;&auml;ratud sadamasse vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1956/88 lisa punkti 10 alapunktile ii. </eesti>
<inglise> The time limit referred to in the first subparagraph may be extended by the Commission at the request of a Member State addressed to the Commission, up to a maximum of 72 hours. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon v&otilde;ib esimeses l&otilde;igus nimetatud t&auml;htaega pikendada k&otilde;ige rohkem 72 tunnini, kui liikmesriik seda komisjonilt taotleb. </eesti>
<inglise> In the event of a diversion, the duly authorized inspector shall take all necessary measures to ensure security and continuity of the evidence including, as appropriate, sealing the vessel's hold for eventual dockside inspection. </inglise>
<eesti> Sadamasse p&ouml;&ouml;rdumise korral v&otilde;tab n&otilde;uetekohaselt volitatud inspektor k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed, et tagada t&otilde;endusmaterjali turvalisus ja s&auml;ilimine, sealhulgas pitseerib vajaduse korral laeva lastiruumi edaspidi sadamas toimuva inspekteerimise tarbeks. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> On arrival at the port of diversion, the suspect vessel shall be the subject of a thorough inspection carried out under the authority of the flag Member State, which may be attended by a NAFO inspector from any other Contracting Party wishing to take part. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kahtlustatav laev saabub m&auml;&auml;ratud sadamasse, l&auml;bib ta lipuliikmesriigi jurisdiktsiooni all p&otilde;hjaliku inspekteerimise, milles v&otilde;ib soovi korral osaleda teise lepinguosalise riigi NAFO inspektor. </eesti>
<inglise> The Flag Member State shall immediately inform the Commission of the results of the inspection, using the form in Annex I to this Regulation, and of the measures it has taken to deal with the infringement. </inglise>
<eesti> Lipuliikmesriik teatab viivitamata komisjonile inspekteerimise tulemustest, kasutades selleks k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse I lisas esitatud vormi, ja meetmetest, mida ta on rikkumisega seoses v&otilde;tnud. </eesti>
<inglise> 7. </inglise>
<eesti> 7. </eesti>
<inglise> In the appropriate authority of the flag state does not require the vessel to be diverted to a port in accordance with paragraph 10 (ii) of the Annex to Regulation (EEC) No 1956/88, it shall immediately inform the Commission of the reasons on which its decision was based. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui lipuriigi p&auml;dev asutus ei anna korraldust laeva p&ouml;&ouml;rdumiseks sadamasse vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1956/88 lisa punkti 10 alapunktile ii, teatab ta viivitamata komisjonile oma otsuse p&otilde;hjenduse. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall in due course inform the Executive Secretariat of NAFO of that decision and of the reasons therefor. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon teatab nimetatud otsusest ja selle p&otilde;hjustest &otilde;igeaegselt NAFO t&auml;itevsekretariaadile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 (b) </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4b </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> When the Community inspectors suspect that a fishing vessel flying the flag of a Contracting Party has committed one of the serious infringements listed in paragraph 9 of the Annex to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1956/88, the inspectors in question shall, within 24 hours, inform the appropriate authorities of the flag state concerned and the Executive Secretariat of NAFO thereof, supplying them with all the elements on the basis of which they cited that vessel for having committed an apparent serious infringement. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui &uuml;henduse inspektorid kahtlustavad, et lepinguosalise lipu all s&otilde;itev kalalaev on sooritanud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1956/88 lisa punktis 9 nimetatud t&otilde;sise rikkumise, teatavad k&otilde;nealused inspektorid sellest 24 tunni jooksul asjaomase lipuriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele ja NAFO t&auml;itevsekretariaadile, esitades neile k&otilde;ik t&otilde;endid, mille alusel nad otsustasid, et see laev on sooritanud ilmse t&otilde;sise rikkumise. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall send the Member States a copy of the notification addressed to the Executive Secretariat of NAFO. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon saadab liikmesriikidele koopia NAFO t&auml;itevsekretariaadile edastatud teatest. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall decide, with the agreement of the Contracting Party responsible for the vessel, if a Community inspector is to remain on board when the vessel is diverted. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon otsustab kokkuleppel laeva eest vastutava lepinguosalisega, kas &uuml;henduse inspektor peab j&auml;&auml;ma sadamasse suunatud laeva pardale. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall also decide if a Community inspector is to be present during the thorough inspection of the suspect vessel, in port. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon otsustab ka selle, kas &uuml;henduse inspektor peab viibima kahtlustatava laeva p&otilde;hjaliku inspekteerimise juures sadamas." </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In Article 9, the introductory words are replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 9 asendatakse sissejuhatavad s&otilde;nad j&auml;rgmistega: </eesti>
<inglise> 'Each Member State shall notify to the Commission by 25 January each year for the period 1 July to 31 December, and by 25 August each year for the period 1 January to 30 June, the information required in points 1 and 2 of this Article, in accordance with the model in Annex II, and also the information required in point 3 of this Article, in accordance with the model in Annex III: ' . </inglise>
